      "content": "thanks. this is exactly the kind of specific stuff we need. i noticed most of these feel very centered on western business norms, like the suits and the handshakes. but our clients go to places like Tokyo, Lagos, or Mumbai too. \n\nhow should we frame the guide so it covers those regions without making them seem \"unprofessional\" or weird? like, should we list these western standards as the \"core\" and then just add a section for \"regional variations\" or \"traditional customs\" for places like Asia or Africa? just want to make sure the guide feels cohesive.",
